Questions:
What is the primary goal of the "Clinical study of stellate ganglion block in the treatment of patients with advanced Parkinson's disease" research?
A) To assess the long-term effects of Parkinson's medication on cognitive function;
B) To evaluate the effectiveness of stellate ganglion block therapy in improving motor and non-motor symptoms in advanced Parkinson's disease patients;
C) To compare the cost-effectiveness of deep brain stimulation versus standard medication in Parkinson's treatment;
D) To investigate the genetic markers associated with Parkinson's disease progression.

Correct answer: B

What alternative treatments are available to subjects who choose not to participate in the stellate ganglion block study for advanced Parkinson's disease?
A) Subjects will be provided with a new experimental drug therapy not yet available to the public;
B) Subjects can receive standard Western medicine treatment and rehabilitation physiotherapy;
C) Subjects will be enrolled in a different clinical trial focusing on surgical interventions for Parkinson's disease;
D) There are no alternative treatments available outside of the study.

Correct answer: B

Who is authorized to review your personal medical information for the purpose of ensuring the research is standardized and the data is true and reliable?

A) Only the principal investigator and the research team;
B) Government regulatory agencies and the ethics committee, in addition to your research doctor;
C) All hospital staff members;
D) Any third-party advertisers or pharmaceutical companies.

Correct answer: B) Government regulatory agencies and the ethics committee, in addition to your research doctor.
